-# The Knowledge Card
.card.border-0.shadow-sm.border-start.border-4.border-info
  .card-body.p-4

    -# --- Header ---
    .d-flex.align-items-center.mb-3
      .bg-info-subtle.text-info-emphasis.rounded-circle.d-flex.align-items-center.justify-content-center.me-3.lh-1{style: "width: 48px; height: 48px"}
        %span.mi.md-24.fill help

      %div
        %h5.fw-bold.text-dark.mb-0 How Roles Work
        %small.text-secondary Privileged roles for system management.

    -# --- Section 1: The Roles (Tiles) ---
    .row.g-3.mb-4
      -# Tile 1: Admin
      .col-md-6
        .d-flex.align-items-start
          .text-info.me-3.lh-1
            %span.mi.md-24 admin_panel_settings
          %div
            %span.fw-bold.d-block.text-dark Administrator
            %small.text-muted.lh-sm
              Full access. Can log in anytime, see all problems, and create or delete users.

      -# Tile 2: TA
      .col-md-6
        .d-flex.align-items-start
          .text-info.me-3.lh-1
            %span.mi.md-24 supervisor_account
          %div
            %span.fw-bold.d-block.text-dark TA
            %small.text-muted.lh-sm
              Helper role for class operations.

    -# --- Divider ---
    %hr.text-secondary-subtle.my-3/

    -# --- Section 2: Guidance ---
    %h6.fw-bold.text-dark.small.text-uppercase.mb-3 Guidance

    .d-flex.flex-column.gap-2
      .d-flex.align-items-start.gap-2
        %span.mi.md-18.text-warning.flex-shrink-0 warning
        %small.text-secondary
          Grant
          %strong.text-dark Administrator
          only when truly required &mdash; admins can create and delete users.

      .d-flex.align-items-start.gap-2
        %span.mi.md-18.text-info.flex-shrink-0 lightbulb
        %small.text-secondary
          For per-group problem setters, prefer the
          %strong.text-dark Editor
          role (managed via Groups) over Administrator.
